git clone https://github.com/username/repo_name local_folder
git fetch (not needed if cloned for the first time - needed later to pull other changes in)
git merge
git pull
git pull --rebase*
git stash

If the username prompt is annoying, change protocols:
git config -l # Find out if you're using https which makes git prompt for the username/password all the time

git config remote.origin.url git@github.com:repo_username/project_name.git # Switch to the git protocol

Better way may be to configure using SSH keys
